            <lb/>
            <p rend="align(centre)">THE HORSE.</p>
            <p rend="first-indent(3) align(justify)">THE horse is the most useful<lb/>to man of all
                animals. In the<lb/>beauty of his form, and the<lb/>ease and the grace of his
                motion<lb/>he also is among the most noted.<lb/>We can better judge of the
                    ex&ndash;<lb type="inWord"/>treme beauty of the horse, by<lb/>viewing him in his
                wild state,<lb/>as shown in the picture on the<lb/>opposite page, than by
                looking<lb/>at him as he exists with us.<lb/>He appears in the greatest
                    per&ndash;<lb type="inWord"/>fection in Arabia, on ever ver&ndash;<lb
                    type="inWord"/>dant plains where he is free,<lb/>and where the climate is
                better<lb/>for him. There wild horses are<lb/>seen in droves. They are<lb/>caught by
                means of ropes and <fw type="footer">18</fw><lb/>
                <pb n="6"/>
                <fw rend="align(centre)">4</fw><lb/> snares hid in the sand. Be&ndash;<lb
                    type="inWord"/>ing by nature mild and gentle,<lb/>he is easily learned to be
                    obe&ndash;<lb type="inWord"/>dient, and being once tamed, he<lb/>never shows a
                wish to return<lb/>to his wild state.</p>
            <p rend="first-indent(3) align(justify)">Many stories are told which<lb/>exhibit the
                remarkable intelli&ndash;<lb type="inWord"/>gence and sagacity of this no&ndash;<lb
                    type="inWord"/>ble animal.</p>
            <figure rend="align(centre)">
                <ic:iconClass>
                    <name>46C131</name>
                    <desc>riding a horse, ass, or mule; rider, horseman</desc>
                </ic:iconClass>
            </figure>
            <fw type="footer" rend="align(right)">17</fw>

            <pb n="7"/>
            <fw rend="align(centre)">5</fw>
            <lb/>
            <figure rend="align(centre)">
                <ic:iconClass>
                    <name>46C131</name>
                    <desc>riding a horse, ass, or mule; rider, horseman</desc>
